                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12476464" author="klaasm" created="Wed, 28 Feb 2007 00:24:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(also includes a two-line change to re-write queries prior to highlighting)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12476526" author="hossman" created="Wed, 28 Feb 2007 05:53:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mike: havne&apos;t looked into the patch, but what i was thinking would make sense for the bq issue back when i last thought about this, was to say:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  if: more then one bq param is specified:&lt;br/&gt;
     then: &lt;br/&gt;
       foreach bq param value:&lt;br/&gt;
         trim the value&lt;br/&gt;
         if: the value is non blank&lt;br/&gt;
            then: parse value as a query and add to the main query&lt;br/&gt;
  else:&lt;br/&gt;
     legacy behavior&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...that should be entirely backwards compatible, and gives people who really need a boolean query with a boost of 1 a way to force it (by adding a &amp;lt;null name=&quot;bq&quot; /&amp;gt; to their appended params)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...we would just have to make sure it was clearly documented&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12477060" author="klaasm" created="Thu, 1 Mar 2007 19:26:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s fine with me.  I suspect too that anyone who knows lucene well enough and is trying to get such a precise query structure would feel comfortable tweaking dismax to create their own reqeust handler.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll update the patch in a few minutes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12477061" author="klaasm" created="Thu, 1 Mar 2007 19:27:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated patch as per Hoss&apos; comments.  This could use a once-over before committing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12477820" author="hossman" created="Sun, 4 Mar 2007 17:30:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mike: patch reads nice and clean to me (didn&apos;t try applying though)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;two nits: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) it would be good to have a test of the case where a boolean with the default boost is specified in one bq, and a seperate blank bq is specified to force the first BQ to be treated as a single query&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) let&apos;s assign  params.getParams(DMP.BQ) to a temp variable so we don&apos;t have to call it twice in three lines.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12478145" author="klaasm" created="Mon, 5 Mar 2007 20:22:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed in r514851&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
